        jTextArea1.setText("Loamy soil is the mixture of sand, clay and silt.\n It contains more moisture, nutrients and \nhumus compared to sandy soil and better \ndrainage compared to clay and silt soil. It has \nthe right water holding capacity needed for \nthe growth of plants.\nLoam soils contain sand, silt and clay in such \nproportions that stickyness and \nnon-adhesiveness are in balance so the soils \nare mouldable but not sticky. Loams are the \n\"friendliest\" soils to cultivate. Clays can absorb \nand hold onto large amounts of water because\n of their sheet structure and large surface area.");
